" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\"> <title>Automation Tools Tech Stack Analysis</title> <style> Professional CSS with: - Clean modern design - Responsive tables - Blue/gray color scheme - Good spacing and typography - Print-friendly styles </style> </head> <body> Include these main sections: 1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY with quick recommendations 2. COMPREHENSIVE COMPARISON TABLE All 9 tools (BrowserAct, ActivePieces, ZeroWork, AgenticFlow, Gumloop, Lutra.ai, Lindy.ai, Relevance.ai, Outscraper) with: - Features with ✓/✗ checkboxes - Pros/Cons - Use cases - Scraping ability ratings - Complexity levels - Pricing - Integration capabilities 3. AI RECOMMENDATION ENGINE section explaining the decision framework 4. DETAILED YOUTUBE PLAYLIST SCRAPING EXAMPLE - Step-by-step SOP for non-developers - Tool recommendations with rationale - Input/output specifications - Cost estimates - Alternative approaches 5. TOOL SELECTION MATRIX Make it comprehensive, professional, and actionable with specific tactical details. Excellent! The document has been created successfully. Let me now add some additional enhancements to make it even more comprehensive and actionable for your needs: Using Tool | Doc Edit Let me view more of the document to see what we have: Using Tool | Doc View Viewing document: 400,500 Great! Let me continue viewing to see the full document structure: Using Tool | Doc View Viewing document: 700,827 Perfect! The document is comprehensive and well-structured. Now let me add one final enhancement - a visual decision tree section that will help users quickly identify the right tool. Let me insert this before the final getting started section: Using Tool | Doc Edit --- a/document.html+++ b/document.html@@ -814,13 +814,192 @@       </tbody> </table> +    <h2>🌳 Quick Decision Tree</h2> + +    <div class=\"recommendation-card\"> +      <h4>Start Here: What's Your Primary Goal?</h4> + +      <p><strong>➡️ Need to SCRAPE DATA from websites?</strong></p> +      <ul> +        <li>Complex/Dynamic websites with anti-bot → <strong>BrowserAct</strong></li> +        <li>Social media (LinkedIn, Facebook, Instagram) → <strong>ZeroWork</strong></li> +        <li>Google Maps/Reviews/Business data → <strong>Outscraper</strong></li> +        <li>YouTube/Video platforms → <strong>ZeroWork</strong> or <strong>BrowserAct</strong></li> +        <li>General web scraping (easy sites) → <strong>Gumloop</strong> or <strong>ZeroWork</strong></li> +      </ul> + +      <p><strong>➡️ Need to AUTOMATE WORKFLOWS?</strong></p> +      <ul> +        <li>Connect apps together (CRM, email, Slack) → <strong>ActivePieces</strong> or <strong>Gumloop</strong></li> +        <li>Marketing automation (content, social media) → <strong>AgenticFlow</strong></li> +        <li>Personal productivity (email, calendar) → <strong>Lindy.ai</strong></li> +        <li>Complex business processes → <strong>Gumloop</strong> or <strong>Relevance.ai</strong></li> +      </ul> + +      <p><strong>➡️ Need AI-POWERED INTELLIGENCE?</strong></p> +      <ul> +        <li>Build AI agent teams → <strong>Relevance.ai</strong></li> +        <li>Natural language automation → <strong>Lutra.ai</strong></li> +        <li>AI content generation → <strong>AgenticFlow</strong></li> +        <li>AI-enhanced workflows → <strong>Lindy.ai</strong> or <strong>Gumloop</strong></li> +      </ul> + +      <p><strong>➡️ BUDGET/SKILL CONSIDERATIONS:</strong></p> +      <ul> +        <li>Complete beginner, no coding → <strong>ZeroWork</strong>, <strong>Lindy.ai</strong>, or <strong>ActivePieces</strong></li> +        <li>Limited budget (free/lifetime deals) → <strong>ZeroWork</strong>, <strong>ActivePieces</strong>, <strong>Gumloop</strong></li> +        <li>Need enterprise features → <strong>Relevance.ai</strong>, <strong>Lutra.ai</strong></li> +        <li>Want maximum control → <strong>BrowserAct</strong>, <strong>Gumloop</strong></li> +      </ul> +    </div> + +    <h2>📚 Knowledge Base & Resources</h2> + +    <div class=\"recommendation-card\"> +      <h4>Tool-Specific Learning Resources</h4> + +      <p><strong>BrowserAct:</strong></p> +      <ul> +        <li>Official Discord community for support</li> +        <li>YouTube tutorials on web scraping</li> +        <li>Integration guides for Make, n8n, Zapier</li> +      </ul> + +      <p><strong>ZeroWork:</strong></p> +      <ul> +        <li>Extensive documentation with visual guides</li> +        <li>Active Facebook community</li> +        <li>AppSumo review section with use case examples</li> +      </ul> + +      <p><strong>ActivePieces:</strong></p> +      <ul> +        <li>Open-source GitHub repository</li> +        <li>Community forum for troubleshooting</li> +        <li>Template library with 100+ ready-made flows</li> +      </ul> + +      <p><strong>Gumloop:</strong></p> +      <ul> +        <li>Comprehensive documentation site</li> +        <li>Reddit community (r/LovedByCreators)</li> +        <li>Weekly webinars and tutorials</li> +      </ul> + +      <p><strong>Relevance.ai:</strong></p> +      <ul> +        <li>Enterprise onboarding support</li> +        <li>Template marketplace with 100+ agent templates</li> +        <li>Active community forum</li> +      </ul> +    </div> + +    <h2>⚠️ Common Pitfalls & How to Avoid Them</h2> + +    <div class=\"recommendation-card\"> +      <h4>YouTube Scraping Specific Issues</h4> + +      <p><strong>Problem: Rate Limiting & Account Bans</strong></p> +      <ul> +        <li><strong>Solution:</strong> Use ZeroWork's built-in rate limiting features</li> +        <li>Set delays between requests (5-10 seconds minimum)</li> +        <li>Use residential proxies for large-scale scraping</li> +        <li>Never scrape more than 100 videos per hour from single account</li> +      </ul> + +      <p><strong>Problem: Dynamic Content Not Loading</strong></p> +      <ul> +        <li><strong>Solution:</strong> Increase wait times after page navigation</li> +        <li>Use scroll actions to trigger lazy-loading content</li> +        <li>Watch for AJAX requests completion</li> +        <li>BrowserAct's live browser view helps debug this</li> +      </ul> + +      <p><strong>Problem: Incomplete Comment Extraction</strong></p> +      <ul> +        <li><strong>Solution:</strong> Implement \"Load More Comments\" clicking loop</li> +        <li>Sort comments by \"Top\" first, then \"Newest\"</li> +        <li>Handle nested replies with recursive extraction</li> +        <li>Set maximum comment depth limit (e.g., 3 levels)</li> +      </ul> + +      <p><strong>Problem: Data Structure Inconsistencies</strong></p> +      <ul> +        <li><strong>Solution:</strong> Add data validation nodes</li> +        <li>Set default values for missing fields</li> +        <li>Use regex for text cleaning</li> +        <li>Test with multiple playlists before full deployment</li> +      </ul> +    </div> + +    <h2>💰 ROI Calculator: Time & Cost Savings</h2> + +    <table class=\"data-table\"> +      <thead> +        <tr> +          <th>Manual Method</th> +          <th>Time Investment</th> +          <th>Automated Solution</th> +          <th>Time Required</th> +          <th>Time Saved</th> +          <th>Annual Savings (@ $50/hr)</th> +        </tr> +      </thead> +      <tbody> +        <tr> +          <td>Manually copying 100 videos + comments</td> +          <td>20 hours</td> +          <td>ZeroWork automation</td> +          <td>2 hours setup + 10 min execution</td> +          <td>~18 hours</td> +          <td>$900 per project</td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td>Weekly social media lead research</td> +          <td>5 hours/week</td> +          <td>ZeroWork + ActivePieces</td> +          <td>4 hours setup + 15 min/week</td> +          <td>260 hours/year</td> +          <td>$13,000/year</td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td>Competitor price monitoring (daily)</td> +          <td>30 min/day</td> +          <td>BrowserAct automation</td> +          <td>3 hours setup + 0 min/day</td> +          <td>180 hours/year</td> +          <td>$9,000/year</td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td>Email + calendar management</td> +          <td>10 hours/week</td> +          <td>Lindy.ai agent</td> +          <td>1 hour setup + 2 hours/week</td> +          <td>416 hours/year</td> +          <td>$20,800/year</td> +        </tr> +      </tbody> +    </table> + <div class=\"summary-box\"> <h3>🚀 Getting Started Recommendations</h3> -      <p><strong>Week 1:</strong> Start with ZeroWork for immediate scraping needs</p> -      <p><strong>Week 2:</strong> Add ActivePieces for workflow automation</p> -      <p><strong>Week 3:</strong> Implement Outscraper for Google-specific data</p> +      <p><strong>Week 1:</strong> Start with ZeroWork for immediate scraping needs (YouTube project)</p> +      <p><strong>Week 2:</strong> Add ActivePieces for workflow automation & app integration</p> +      <p><strong>Week 3:</strong> Implement Outscraper for Google-specific data (Maps, Reviews)</p> <p><strong>Month 2:</strong> Explore advanced tools (BrowserAct, Gumloop) as needs grow</p> +      <p><strong>Month 3:</strong> Add AI capabilities with Lindy.ai for personal automation</p> <p><strong>Long-term:</strong> Consider Relevance.ai or Lutra.ai for AI-powered workflows</p> + +      <h4>🎯 Your Immediate Action Plan:</h4> +      <ol> +        <li><strong>Today:</strong> Log into ZeroWork and test with 1 small YouTube playlist (10 videos)</li> +        <li><strong>Tomorrow:</strong> Build the full workflow following the SOP above</li> +        <li><strong>Day 3:</strong> Test with your target playlists and refine</li> +        <li><strong>Week 1:</strong> Schedule automation to run weekly/monthly</li> +        <li><strong>Week 2:</strong> Document your workflow and create templates for future use</li> +      </ol> + +      <p><strong>Need Help?</strong> Each tool has active communities. Don't hesitate to ask questions!</p> </div> </body> </html> Perfect! Now let me add one final section - a visual scoring system that will help make quick decisions. Let me add this after the Tool Selection Matrix: Using Tool | Doc Edit --- a/document.html+++ b/document.html@@ -814,6 +814,146 @@       </tbody> </table> +    <h2>📊 Tool Scoring Matrix (Rate Your Project Needs)</h2> + +    <div class=\"recommendation-card\"> +      <h4>How to Use This Scoring System</h4> +      <p>Rate each criterion (1-5) for your project, then match with the tool that scores highest in those areas.</p> +    </div> + +    <table class=\"data-table\"> +      <thead> +        <tr> +          <th>Tool</th> +          <th>Ease of Use (5=easiest)</th> +          <th>Scraping Power (5=best)</th> +          <th>AI Integration (5=best)</th> +          <th>Cost Value (5=best)</th> +          <th>Learning Curve (5=fastest)</th> +          <th>Reliability (5=most reliable)</th> +          <th>Support Quality (5=best)</th> +          <th>TOTAL SCORE</th> +        </tr> +      </thead> +      <tbody> +        <tr> +          <td><strong>BrowserAct</strong></td> +          <td>3/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>3/5</td> +          <td>3/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td><strong>27/35</strong></td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td><strong>ActivePieces</strong></td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>2/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td><strong>29/35</strong></td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td><strong>ZeroWork</strong></td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>3/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td><strong>30/35</strong> ⭐</td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td><strong>AgenticFlow</strong></td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>2/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>3/5</td> +          <td>3/5</td> +          <td><strong>27/35</strong></td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td><strong>Gumloop</strong></td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td><strong>28/35</strong></td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td><strong>Lutra.ai</strong></td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>3/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>3/5</td> +          <td>3/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td><strong>26/35</strong></td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td><strong>Lindy.ai</strong></td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>2/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>3/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td><strong>28/35</strong></td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td><strong>Relevance.ai</strong></td> +          <td>3/5</td> +          <td>3/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>2/5</td> +          <td>2/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td><strong>25/35</strong></td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td><strong>Outscraper</strong></td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>2/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>5/5</td> +          <td>4/5</td> +          <td><strong>30/35</strong> ⭐</td> +        </tr> +      </tbody> +    </table> + +    <div class=\"recommendation-card\"> +      <h4>🏆 Winner Analysis</h4> +      <p><strong>ZeroWork (30/35)</strong> - Best all-around tool for non-developers doing regular scraping and automation. Excellent balance of power, ease, and cost.</p> +      <p><strong>Outscraper (30/35)</strong> - Unbeatable for Google-specific data (Maps, Reviews). Extremely beginner-friendly with instant results.</p> +      <p><strong>ActivePieces (29/35)</strong> - Top choice for pure workflow automation without heavy scraping needs. Free and powerful.</p> + +      <h4>📈 Category Winners:</h4> +      <ul> +        <li><strong>Best for Scraping:</strong> BrowserAct & ZeroWork (tie 5/5)</li> +        <li><strong>Best for AI:</strong> Relevance.ai, Lutra.ai, Lindy.ai, AgenticFlow (tie 5/5)</li> +        <li><strong>Easiest to Learn:</strong> ActivePieces, AgenticFlow, Lindy.ai, Outscraper (tie 5/5)</li> +        <li><strong>Best Value:</strong> ZeroWork, ActivePieces (tie 5/5)</li> +        <li><strong>Most Reliable:</strong> BrowserAct, Relevance.ai, Outscraper (tie 5/5)</li> +      </ul> +    </div> + <h2>🌳 Quick Decision Tree</h2> <div class=\"recommendation-card\"> Excellent! Now let me add one more critical section - troubleshooting and FAQ for the YouTube project specifically: Using Tool | Doc Edit --- a/document.html+++ b/document.html@@ -1034,6 +1034,98 @@       </ul> </div> +    <h2>❓ FAQ: YouTube Playlist Scraping Project</h2> + +    <div class=\"recommendation-card\"> +      <h4>Q: Can I scrape private or unlisted playlists?</h4> +      <p><strong>A:</strong> Yes, but you need to be logged into your YouTube account. In ZeroWork:</p> +      <ul> +        <li>Add \"Login\" step before navigation</li> +        <li>Save cookies for subsequent runs</li> +        <li>Ensure your account has access to the playlist</li> +        <li>Be extra cautious with rate limiting when logged in</li> +      </ul> + +      <h4>Q: How do I handle playlists with 1000+ videos?</h4> +      <p><strong>A:</strong> Break it into batches:</p> +      <ul> +        <li>YouTube only loads ~200 videos at a time initially</li> +        <li>Use pagination detection (YouTube uses infinite scroll)</li> +        <li>Add checkpoints to save progress every 100 videos</li> +        <li>Consider running overnight for very large playlists</li> +        <li>Estimated time: 1-2 seconds per video = 30-60 minutes for 1000 videos</li> +      </ul> + +      <h4>Q: What if YouTube changes its layout?</h4> +      <p><strong>A:</strong> This is why visual tools like ZeroWork are valuable:</p> +      <ul> +        <li>ZeroWork's visual selector makes it easy to update CSS selectors</li> +        <li>Join ZeroWork community to get layout change notifications</li> +        <li>Keep a backup of working selectors</li> +        <li>Test workflow monthly even if not actively using</li> +      </ul> + +      <h4>Q: Can I extract video transcripts/captions?</h4> +      <p><strong>A:</strong> Yes, but requires additional steps:</p> +      <ul> +        <li>Navigate to each video page (adds time)</li> +        <li>Click \"Show transcript\" button</li> +        <li>Extract transcript text</li> +        <li>This significantly increases scraping time (3-5x longer)</li> +        <li>Consider using YouTube API for captions (requires API key)</li> +      </ul> + +      <h4>Q: How do I track which playlists I've already scraped?</h4> +      <p><strong>A:</strong> Create a tracking system:</p> +      <ul> +        <li>Add a \"Playlists\" sheet with: Playlist Name, URL, Last Scraped Date, Video Count</li> +        <li>Use Google Sheets lookup to check if playlist already exists</li> +        <li>Add timestamp column to track when data was extracted</li> +        <li>Set up conditional logic to skip or update existing playlists</li> +      </ul> + +      <h4>Q: What about comment sentiment analysis or AI processing?</h4> +      <p><strong>A:</strong> Add AI layer after scraping:</p> +      <ul> +        <li>Primary scrape: ZeroWork → Google Sheets</li> +        <li>AI processing: Gumloop or Lutra.ai reads from Sheets</li> +        <li>Sentiment analysis using GPT-4 or Claude</li> +        <li>Write results back to additional columns</li> +        <li>Estimated cost: $0.01-0.05 per comment for AI processing</li> +      </ul> + +      <h4>Q: Can I automate this to run weekly?</h4> +      <p><strong>A:</strong> Absolutely:</p> +      <ul> +        <li>ZeroWork supports scheduling (every 5 min to monthly)</li> +        <li>Set to run weekly on Sunday night (low traffic time)</li> +        <li>Configure notifications on completion or errors</li> +        <li>Monitor first 2-3 runs to ensure reliability</li> +        <li>Set up email alerts for failures</li> +      </ul> + +      <h4>Q: What's the legal/ethical position on scraping YouTube?</h4> +      <p><strong>A:</strong> Important considerations:</p> +      <ul> +        <li>✅ Public data scraping is generally legal (US precedent: hiQ Labs v. LinkedIn)</li> +        <li>✅ You're accessing publicly available data same as browser</li> +        <li>⚠️ Respect YouTube Terms of Service - don't overwhelm servers</li> +        <li>⚠️ Don't sell scraped data commercially without verification</li> +        <li>⚠️ Use reasonable rate limiting (act like a human)</li> +        <li>💡 For commercial use, consider YouTube Data API v3 (official, rate-limited, free tier available)</li> +      </ul> + +      <h4>Q: My scraping stopped working mid-process. What happened?</h4> +      <p><strong>A:</strong> Common causes and fixes:</p> +      <ul> +        <li><strong>Rate limiting:</strong> Pause for 1 hour, then resume with slower speed</li> +        <li><strong>Cookie expiration:</strong> Re-login and save new cookies</li> +        <li><strong>Network timeout:</strong> Increase wait times in your workflow</li> +        <li><strong>YouTube CAPTCHA:</strong> BrowserAct handles these better than ZeroWork</li> +        <li><strong>Browser crash:</strong> Set up auto-restart and checkpointing</li> +      </ul> +    </div> + <h2>⚠️ Common Pitfalls & How to Avoid Them</h2> <div class=\"recommendation-card\"> Perfect! Now let me add one final enhancement - a comprehensive checklist and quality assurance section before the ROI calculator: Using Tool | Doc Edit --- a/document.html+++ b/document.html@@ -1164,6 +1164,127 @@       </ul> </div> +    <h2>✅ Pre-Launch Checklist: YouTube Scraping Project</h2> + +    <div class=\"recommendation-card\"> +      <h4>Before You Start (Setup Phase)</h4> +      <p>☐ ZeroWork account created and verified<br> +      ☐ AppSumo lifetime deal activated (if applicable)<br> +      ☐ Google Sheets connected via OAuth<br> +      ☐ Test spreadsheet created with proper column headers<br> +      ☐ YouTube account logged in (if scraping private playlists)<br> +      ☐ Identified 1 small test playlist (10-20 videos)<br> +      ☐ Rate limiting strategy determined (requests per hour)<br> +      ☐ Backup plan identified (e.g., BrowserAct as fallback)</p> + +      <h4>During Build Phase</h4> +      <p>☐ Workflow created with descriptive name<br> +      ☐ All nodes properly connected and tested individually<br> +      ☐ Error handling added (what happens if element not found?)<br> +      ☐ Data validation nodes included<br> +      ☐ Progress logging enabled<br> +      ☐ Checkpointing configured (save every 50-100 videos)<br> +      ☐ Anti-ban delays added (5-10 seconds between requests)<br> +      ☐ Cookie acceptance handled<br> +      ☐ Infinite scroll detection working<br> +      ☐ Comment expansion logic tested</p> + +      <h4>Testing Phase</h4> +      <p>☐ Test run completed with 1 small playlist (10 videos)<br> +      ☐ All expected data fields populated in Google Sheets<br> +      ☐ No duplicate entries<br> +      ☐ Comments properly nested and attributed<br> +      ☐ Timestamps accurate<br> +      ☐ URLs formatted correctly<br> +      ☐ Special characters handled (emojis, foreign languages)<br> +      ☐ Missing data fields have default values<br> +      ☐ Test run #2 with medium playlist (50-100 videos)<br> +      ☐ Workflow completed without errors</p> + +      <h4>Production Phase</h4> +      <p>☐ Scheduling configured (if automating)<br> +      ☐ Email notifications set up for completion/errors<br> +      ☐ Documentation created (how to run, troubleshoot)<br> +      ☐ Backup workflow exported and saved<br> +      ☐ Google Sheets shared with relevant team members<br> +      ☐ Monitoring plan established (check weekly)<br> +      ☐ Maintenance calendar created (test monthly)<br> +      ☐ Escalation plan if workflow breaks</p> + +      <h4>Optimization Phase (After 2-3 Successful Runs)</h4> +      <p>☐ Speed optimizations identified<br> +      ☐ Unnecessary delays removed<br> +      ☐ Parallel processing considered (if scraping multiple playlists)<br> +      ☐ Data cleaning automated with formulas/scripts<br> +      ☐ Reporting dashboard created from scraped data<br> +      ☐ Template created for future similar projects<br> +      ☐ Cost tracking implemented<br> +      ☐ ROI calculated and documented</p> +    </div> + +    <h2>🔍 Quality Assurance: Data Validation Tests</h2> + +    <table class=\"data-table\"> +      <thead> +        <tr> +          <th>Test</th> +          <th>What to Check</th> +          <th>Expected Result</th> +          <th>Action if Fails</th> +        </tr> +      </thead> +      <tbody> +        <tr> +          <td>Video Count Match</td> +          <td>Number of videos in sheet = playlist count</td> +          <td>100% match (±2 for recent uploads)</td> +          <td>Check infinite scroll detection</td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td>URL Validity</td> +          <td>All video URLs are clickable and valid</td> +          <td>0 broken links</td> +          <td>Review URL extraction selector</td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td>Duplicate Detection</td> +          <td>No duplicate video IDs in sheet</td> +          <td>All unique entries</td> +          <td>Add de-duplication node</td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td>Comment Attribution</td> +          <td>Comments linked to correct video</td> +          <td>100% accuracy</td> +          <td>Check data structure/relationships</td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td>Special Characters</td> +          <td>Emojis, quotes, non-English text preserved</td> +          <td>All characters display correctly</td> +          <td>Check text encoding settings</td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td>Timestamp Accuracy</td> +          <td>Dates/times are current and formatted consistently</td> +          <td>Correct timezone and format</td> +          <td>Adjust timestamp extraction</td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td>Missing Data Handling</td> +          <td>Empty fields have \"N/A\" or default value</td> +          <td>No blank cells in critical columns</td> +          <td>Add default value nodes</td> +        </tr> +        <tr> +          <td>Performance Test</td> +          <td>100 videos extracted in under 15 minutes</td> +          <td>Acceptable speed maintained</td> +          <td>Optimize delays and selectors</td> +        </tr> +      </tbody> +    </table> + <h2>💰 ROI Calculator: Time & Cost Savings</h2> <table class=\"data-table\"> Excellent! Now let me add a comprehensive visual styling improvement and a final \"Next Steps\" action plan section. Let me update the CSS to make it even more professional: Using Tool | Doc Edit --- a/document.html+++ b/document.html@@ -138,6 +138,98 @@         background-color: #4a5568; color: white; } + +      .warning-box { +        background-color: #fff5f0; +        border-left: 4px solid #ed8936; +        padding: 15px; +        margin: 15px 0; +      } + +      .success-box { +        background-color: #f0fff4; +        border-left: 4px solid #48bb78; +        padding: 15px; +        margin: 15px 0; +      } + +      .info-box { +        background-color: #ebf8ff; +        border-left: 4px solid #4299e1; +        padding: 15px; +        margin: 15px 0; +      } + +      .tool-badge { +        display: inline-block; +        background-color: #4299e1; +        color: white; +        padding: 3px 8px; +        border-radius: 3px; +        font-size: 11px; +        font-weight: bold; +        margin: 2px; +      } + +      .difficulty-easy { +        colo"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=0de4230f-fa91-40b7-bb97-ac1942640042","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=0de4230f-fa91-40b7-bb97-ac1942640042"}]}]}]
